President Biden invited labor representatives into the Oval Office to discuss the importance of labor and the need to rebuild infrastructure in the country. He emphasized that the middle class built the country and that labor built the middle class. The President expressed his commitment to creating good-paying jobs and rebuilding the country's infrastructure. He also mentioned the need to pass the Recovery Act and highlighted the importance of infrastructure for the nation's competitiveness. President Biden stated that American workers and the economy will experience significant growth. He mentioned that polling data shows that the American people support the plan and want assistance with nutrition, mortgages, unemployment insurance, and housing stability. The President emphasized that the federal government needs to contribute in order to address these issues and generate income for those in need. He also mentioned that major economists and the International Monetary Fund believe the plan will grow the economy. President Biden concluded the meeting by thanking everyone for attending.